Intraoral cameras have gained significant popularity in the dental industry due to their ability to provide clear and detailed images of the oral cavity, aiding in diagnosis and treatment planning. The market for intraoral cameras can be segmented based on type, application, end-user, and region. In terms of type, the market is divided into wired intraoral cameras and wireless intraoral cameras. Wired intraoral cameras are connected to a monitor or a computer for image display, while wireless ones offer more flexibility and convenience with their cordless nature. From an application perspective, intraoral cameras are used for diagnosis, therapeutic purposes, and other applications within the dental field. End-users of these cameras include hospitals, dental clinics, and other healthcare facilities. Geographically, the market is segmented into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa.

